properties.abstract: The Frstensteig is one of the most famous paths of the Rtikon mountain range and is a classic mountain hike in Liechtenstein. A first class tour full of extremes and surprises awaits you.
properties.description:
The hike begins with the scenic views from alp Gaflei at an altitude of 1,400 meters above sea level. Over green pastures and past mountain pines, the path climbs continuously to reveal spectacular views.  Frstensteig is an experience of a special kind. The exposed parts are secured with wire ropes and railing to hold on to.  At the Gaflei saddle we can see the Drei Schwestern mountains in the distance. We will hike below the Schrofen mountain peak up a steep path through a gap, below the Helwangs peak, to the Kamin which is also sign-posted as the Chemi (Chimney).

From the Kamin, the path takes you past more mountain pines down to Barglla saddle where a view of all the Liechtenstein mountains and their valleys and peaks can be seen. Now it's only a short hike back to the starting point in Gaflei.
